# Fluff Date: 2026-02-09 16:25:29
overview:<p>The Aquagladius emerged from the innovative workshops of Vining Engineering and Salvage Team during the mid-3050s, when VEST sought to establish itself in the competitive Solaris VII arena market. While other design firms focused on conventional gladiatorial combat, VEST identified an underserved niche in the underwater arenas of Solaris. The result was one of the most unconventional BattleMech designs ever produced—a dedicated aquatic combat platform built on the proven Crab chassis.</p><p>VEST's reputation for innovative if controversial designs drew both admiration and criticism. Competitors like Omnitech Industries and Solaris Arms dismissed the Aquagladius and its sibling design, the Great Turtle, as white elephants whose excessive cost and narrow focus made them little more than glorified IndustrialMechs. Despite this criticism, limited success in the arenas sparked interest, proving that performance matters more than reputation when PPCs discharge and autocannons blaze.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Aquagladius incorporates numerous experimental systems optimized for underwater combat. Pioneering underwater maneuvering units allow the fifty-ton 'Mech to achieve 83 percent of its walking speed while submerged—unprecedented mobility for a design of its mass. The chassis is based on a Hollis Mark 2B frame derived from the Crab, with extensive modifications to the fluid dynamics and armor placement that reflect its aquatic origins.</p><p>VEST loaded the design with bleeding-edge technology, including a light engine purchased from Wolf's Dragoons, a BattleMech taser acquired from NAIS, and a prototype HarJel system to prevent flooding when armor is breached. A flail provides devastating close-range striking power against disabled opponents. Light ferro-fibrous armor mounted on an endo steel skeleton maximizes protection while minimizing weight, though this complexity contributes to the Aquagladius's reputation for difficult maintenance.</p>

deployment:<p>Designated the Marine Assault 'Mech, the AQS-5 MAM was developed in 3090 specifically for the Republic Armed Forces. A 300-rated XXL engine and triple-strength myomer dramatically increase speed and physical combat capability, while a heavy PPC with capacitor provides devastating ranged firepower. Twin small variable speed pulse lasers and extended-range flamers round out the armament. A MechWarrior Aquatic Survival System replaces the HarJel, prioritizing pilot safety over 'Mech preservation. This variant equipped a dedicated amphibious company on Terra that trained extensively but saw no combat through 3135.</p>

history:<p>The Aquagladius first made its mark in the Bracken Swamp's Pool arena, where the AQS-3 belonging to Banshees Stables proved a holy terror in underwater combat. The design's dominance was so complete that talk of handicapping it for betting purposes quickly made the rounds, with many considering it to have an unfair advantage in the Pool. A mercenary unit, whose identity VEST refuses to divulge due to a confidentiality clause, purchased the AQS-4 variant, demonstrating interest beyond the Solaris arena circuit.</p><p>The Jihad brought unexpected relevance to this arena curiosity. During Operation SCOUR and the invasion of Terra, coalition forces employed Aquagladius 'Mechs in waterborne assaults against Word of Blake positions. The Republic of the Sphere subsequently commissioned VEST to develop a militarized variant, resulting in the AQS-5 MAM. Designed by VEST engineer Consuela Banana-Hammock, this marine assault 'Mech equipped a dedicated amphibious warfare company stationed on Terra, though the force saw no combat through 3135.</p><p>The Aquagladius demonstrated that designs created for entertainment could find unexpected military applications. VEST has leveraged the design's success to fund development of other projects with an eye toward Republic Armed Forces contracts.</p>

